edu.stanford.nlp.ling
Class AbstractMapLabel

java.lang.Object
  edu.stanford.nlp.ling.AbstractMapLabel
All Implemented Interfaces:
HasCategory, HasContext, HasOffset, HasTag, HasWord, Label, Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
FeatureLabel
public abstract class AbstractMapLabel
extends Object
implements Label, HasWord, HasTag, HasCategory, HasContext, HasOffset, Serializable

An abstract class for Label objects which store attributes in a Map. Also implements HasWord, HasTag, HasCategory, and HasContext by storing the words, tags, etc. under standardized keys in the Map.

For convenience, this class also contains standardized keys for storing many other possible label attributes, such as head words, ner tags, etc.

Author:
grenager

PROJ_CAT_KEY

public static final String PROJ_CAT_KEY
The standard key for storing a projected category in the map, as a String. For any word (leaf node), the projected category is the syntactic category of the maximal constituent headed by the word. Used in SemanticGraph.

put

Associates the specified value with the specified key in the map contained in this label. (Analogous to Map.put(Object key, Object value).) If the map previously contained a mapping for this key, the old value is replaced by the specified value.

Parameters:

setIndex

public void setIndex(int index)
Set the index for the label by storing it in the contained map under the key INDEX_KEY. WARNING: do NOT call this if the vertice is already in a SemanticGraph. Doing so will disrupt the equality criteria for the map, and will throw off routines that check to see if this vertice is in the SemanticGraph.
